{{About|a type of theater technology|other uses|magazine (disambiguation)}}
[[File:FSboomerang.JPG|thumb|right|220 px|An example of a color magazine or "boomerang"]] A '''color magazine''' is a fixture attached to a [[follow spot]] that places different color filters in the path of the beam. Instead of working with comparatively cumbersome [[color gel|gel]] frames, the color magazine allows the spot operator to easily slide color frames in or out of place using a series of levers.
The term '''boomerang''' is also used to describe a color magazine.<ref>{{Cite book | last = Box | first = Harry | authorlink = | coauthors = | title = Set Lighting Technician's Handbook | edition = 3rd | publisher = [[Focal Press]] | year = 2003 | location = Burlington, MA | pages = 273 | url = https://books.google.com/?id=YjAzP4i1oFcC | doi = | id = | isbn = 978-0-240-80495-8}} </ref>
Color magazines are now becoming rarer with the widespread availability of programmable-colour [[LED lighting]].
